The paper discusses the use of neural architectures for learning problems in relational domains, specifically focusing on Graph Neural Networks. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given the focus on neural architectures and machine learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV due to the mention of convolutional neural networks. The mention of message-passing iterations also suggests relevance to cs.CL, and the use of trainable neural modules suggests relevance to cs.NE.
